![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

Use the `useLocation` hook to get the current location. This is preferred over using the global `location` object in TanStack Start applications to ensure consistency during server-side rendering and to allow the `useEffect` to correctly track location changes if they occur while the session is loading.

```suggestion
  const router = useRouter();
  const location = useLocation();
```

![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

Add `location.href` to the dependency array of the `useEffect`. This ensures that if the user navigates to a different protected URL while the session is still being fetched, the `redirect` parameter will be updated to the most recent location when the effect eventually triggers the navigation.

```suggestion
  }, [router, session.data?.user, session.error, session.isPending, location.href]);
```

_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Redirect guard and render guard are inconsistent, causing a blank state for some auth errors.**

If `session.error` exists but does not satisfy `session.error.status > 0`, the effect skips navigation while render returns `null` for no user. That creates a no-UI/no-redirect path.


<details>
<summary>💡 Suggested fix</summary>

```diff
   useEffect(() => {
-    if (session.isPending || session.error || session.data?.user) {
+    const blockingError = session.error && session.error.status > 0;
+    if (session.isPending || blockingError || session.data?.user) {
       return;
     }

     router.navigate({
       to: '/login',
       replace: true,
       search: {
         redirect: location.href,
       },
     });
-  }, [router, session.data?.user, session.error, session.isPending]);
+  }, [router, session.data?.user, session.error, session.isPending]);
```
</details>


Also applies to: 39-45

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the
rest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.

In `@src/features/auth/guard-authenticated.tsx` around lines 22 - 24, The render
guard and the effect use inconsistent predicates (render returns null when
!session.data?.user but the effect only redirects when session.error.status >
0), causing a blank state when session.error exists without a positive status;
fix by making the redirect/effect and the render use the same predicate: use
session.isPending, session.error (truthy), and session.data?.user consistently.
For example, update the effect and render to derive a single boolean (e.g.,
const isUnauthenticated = !session.isPending && (!session.data?.user ||
!!session.error)) and use that in both the navigation logic and the component
return so any session.error triggers the redirect or the same UI path. Ensure
you change the checks that reference session.isPending, session.error, and
session.data?.user so they match exactly in both places.
```

</details>

